  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Space Enabled monitoring of Illegal Gold Mining Call 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Unregulated gold mining is a billion-dollar
trade which causes devastating impacts
nationally; specifically on local communities
and the environment. Mercury is frequently
used by informal mining operations to
extract the gold from the ore; it then enters
the environment through many mechanisms:
&#x2022; Smelting operations in local towns creating
atmospheric pollution
&#x2022; Seepage into the surrounding soil
&#x2022; Leaching into rivers, impacting the food
chain.
These different pollution pathways lead to
devastating environmental degradation
and serious health problems such as kidney
failure, acute anaemia and brain damage in
new-borns.
Colombia&#x2019;s new post-conflict government
has set ambitious goals to reform the gold
mining sector, but significant challenges
remain. One key challenge is the ability
of authorities to detect unauthorised gold
mining in its remote forested areas in near
real-time, allowing the ability to monitor their
progress in managing legal gold mining.</narrative>
  </description>
